{{current}}

[[File:Centre Block - Parliament Hill.jpg|right|thumb|Parliament Hill's Centre Block, where the shooter was reportedly shot dead.<ref name="CBC live" />]]
The '''2014 Canadian Parliament Hill attack''' began on October 22, 2014 when one gunman shot a [[Canadian Forces]] soldier outside the [[National War Memorial (Canada)|Canadian National War Memorial]] in [[Ottawa]], [[Ontario]], [[Canada]]. The gunman then proceeded into the [[Parliament of Canada|Canadian Parliament buildings]], where he was reportedly shot dead.<ref name="CBC live">[http://www.cbc.ca/news/politics/parliament-hill-attacked-soldier-shot-at-national-war-memorial-in-ottawa-1.2808710 Parliament Hill attacked, soldier shot at National War Memorial in Ottawa]</ref>

Subsequent to this initial shooting, there are reports of other suspects and shots fired off of [[Parliament Hill]].<ref name="CBC live" /> The attack comes after two Canadian Forces soldiers were struck by an [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|ISIL]] sympathizer in a car, killing one of them, and after Canada raised its terror threat level from low to medium.<ref> [http://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-29724907?ns_mchannel=social&ns_campaign=bbc_breaking&ns_source=twitter&ns_linkname=news_central Shots fired inside Canada parliament]</ref>

